2026-04-14 — D1 sync: duplicate widget rows + clothing metadata
- Root cause (widgets): `replace_widgets` only matched by DB `id`; companion/mirror clients often PUT without `id` (GET race, cache-only load) → new SQLite row per save → multiple D1 rows per `widget_id` (upsert is by `id` only).
- Fix: `backend/services/widget_service.py` `replace_widgets` — fall back to match by `widget_id` (canonical lowest existing `id`), then delete initial rows not in `seen_ids`.
- Clothing: D1 only mirrors what exists on the Pi SQLite after successful upload + `d1_sync` push (`clothing_item` then `clothing_image`); failed Cloudinary/missing `CLOUDINARY_URL` means no `clothing_image` rows to sync. Check Pi logs for `D1 push failed for clothing_image`. Old duplicate `widget_config` rows in D1 may remain until manually removed or DB reset.
